http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/3i-0&fd=R&url=http://www.finfacts.com/irelandbusinessnews/publish/article_1010230.shtml&cid=1116840694&ei=muxeRt2jO5CUrgOCrPHUDQ US GDP growth in Q1 2007 revised down to annual rate of 0.6% Click for the Finfacts Ireland Portal Homepage Finfacts Business News Centre How to use our RSS feed Finfacts is Ireland's leading business information site and you are in its business news section. We provide access to live business television and business related videos from: Bloomberg TV; The Wall Street Journal; CNBC and the Financial Times. Click image: May 31st, 2007 - 13:52:58 US GDP growth in Q1 2007 revised down to annual rate of 0.6% May 31, 2007, 13:42 Source: Bureau of Economic Analysis The US economy grew at an annual rate of 0.6 percent in the first quarter, according to the "preliminary" estimates released by the US Bureau of Economic Analysis. Based on newly available data that showed a marked reduction in business inventories and a surge in imports in March, the GDP growth rate was revised down 0.7 percentage point from the "advance" estimate of 1.3 percent. BEA also released its first estimate of first-quarter corporate profits. Gross Domestic Product (GDP) The deceleration in first-quarter GDP growth primarily reflected a downturn in net exports. First-quarter corporate profits increased 6.3 percent from the same quarter a year ago. In the fourth quarter, profits grew 18.3 percent. Profits of financial corporations increased 13.1 percent in the first quarter, and profits of nonfinancial corporations decreased 0.4 percent. Source: Bureau of Economic Analysis &copy; Copyright 2007 by Finfacts.com US GDP growth in Q1 2007 revised down to annual rate of 0.6% India's economy grew at the fastest pace in almost 20 years in year to March 31, 2007 Thursday Newspaper Review - Irish Business News and International Stories China's GDP growth forecast at 10.4% in 2007 Ernst & Young Partners charged in US Tax Shelter case Chinese sh