y takeovers as it allows buyers to maintain control while diluting risk. Mr Ackmanâ€™s reaction to the deal will be key to its fate. He could not be reached for comment last night. Relational sold its stake in Ceridian earlier this year. Deutsche Bank is advising the buyers. The Financial Times Limited 2007 - create a keyword alert on the subject of this topic - download our application to receive instant alerts on this topic - start your day with daily email briefing on this topic - Track this news topic using our feeds "Middle East" sub navigation "By sector" sub navigation "By region" sub navigation "Markets headlines" sub navigation "Market data" sub navigation Australia & New Zealand "Managed funds" sub navigation "Comment & Analysis" sub navigation Comment & Analysis main "Debates and polls" sub navigation Debates and polls main "Video & Audio" sub navigation Video & Audio main View from the Top "Business Life" sub navigation "Business education" sub navigation Features of the week "Your Money" sub navigation "Advice & comment" sub navigation Advice & comment main "Compare & apply" sub navigation Compare & apply main "Arts & Weekend" sub navigation Arts & Weekend main How to spend it "Weekend columnists" sub navigation "In depth" sub navigation "Special Reports" sub navigation "Jobs & classified" sub navigation Jobs & classified main "Services & tools" sub navigation Services & tools main "News tracking" sub navigation Investment Banking & Brokerage Minimum delay 15 minutes All times are London time Advertise with the FT The Financial Times Ltd 2007. "FT" and "Financial Times" are trademarks of The Financial Times Ltd. Type your search criteria below: FINANCIAL ADMINISTRATOR / BURSAR Fund Management Company For Sale Retailer Of Oriental/Decorative Carpets Edinburgh, Lothian, United Kingdom Printers With Spare Capacity? Traditional Silversmiths Plant and Equipment Sheffield, South Yorkshire, United Kingdom Republic of Azerbaijan Tender Announcement Tenders Invi