http://news.google.com/news/url?sa=T&ct=us/0-0&fd=R&url=http://moneycentral.msn.com/inc/news/providerredir.asp%3Ffeed%3DAP%26Date%3D20070604%26ID%3D6990035&cid=1116950216&ei=iIBkRpfiIaPkqQPqq_SfBg Associated Press Business News: Sector Snap: Smartphone Stocks Rise - MSN Money Enter name or tic June 4, 2007 1:28 PM ET Sector Snap: Smartphone Stocks Rise Stocks mentioned in this article Nokia Corporation (ADR) ( RESEARCH IN MOTION LIMITED ( All Associated Press News NEW YORK (AP) - Shares of smartphone makers rose Monday after smartphone maker Palm Inc. said it will sell a 25 percent stake to Elevation Partners, a private equity firm, for $325 million. Under the deal, which was announced Monday, Palm will pay shareholders a special distribution of $9 per share -- a total of about $940 milion in cash. Palm shares added 1.34, or 8.3 percent, to $17.44 in trading Monday. The company also said former Apple Inc. hardware engineer Jon Rubenstein will become Palm's chairman. Rubenstein helped bring Apple's iMac computer to fruition and headed the company's iPod unit between 2004 and 2006. In addition, Palm said board members D. Scott Mercer and Eric Benhamou -- a former Palm chief executive -- will resign and Elevation partners Fred Anderson and Roger McNamee will become part of Palm's board. On Monday a Bear Stearns analyst also increased their rating for Palm to "Peer Perform" from "Underperform." A smartphone is a mobile phone with personal computer-like functionality that typically includes a camera phone, full-featured email capabilities with the functionality of a personal organizer. Meanwhile, shares of Palm competitor Research In Motion Ltd. rose $1.93 to $167. Elsewhere in the sector, shares of Apple rose after the company confirmed its anticipated iPhone device -- which combines a phone, media player and wireless Internet access -- will be launched on June 29. Apple gained $1.34 to $119.75 in afternoon trading. On Sunday, commercials stating the date and reiterating its availability "Only on the new AT&T" began airing. Apple also posted the ads on its Web site, and a company spokesman confirmed the date is correct. Shares of cell phone maker Motorola Inc. also grew in trading, gaining 4 cents to $18.32 in the afternoon. Also Monday, a CIBC analyst upgraded their rating on the stock to "Sector Outperform" from "Sector Perform." Cell phone maker Nokia Corp. added 25 cents to $28.44 in afternoon trading. &#169; 2007 The Associated Press. All rights reserved. This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed. Back to News Home
