ibb Co. increased after reports showed the companies&#39; drugs provided advances against cancer. Onyx Pharmaceuticals surged $2.38 to $33.26 in Germany and Bristol-Myers Squibb climbed 38 cents to $30.86. Health Care Property Investors Inc. may move. Segro Plc, owner of five of the U.K.&#39;s largest business parks, plans to sell its U.S. arm to Health Care Property Investors for $2.9 billion. Palm Inc. surged 98 cents to $17.07 in Germany. The maker of the Treo mobile phone and e-mail device agreed to sell a 25 percent stake to private-equity firm Elevation Partners for $325 million and announced an overhaul of its board. Palm will pay $940 million in cash, or about $9 a share, to existing shareholders, financing that with the $325 million from Elevation, $400 million of new debt and existing cash on its balance sheet, the Sunnyvale, California-based company said in a statement on Business Wire today. Nike Inc., the world&#39;s largest athletic-shoe maker, gained 69 cents to $57.38 in Germany, after Citigroup Inc. raised its price estimate on the stock by 12 percent to $65. Wal-Mart Stores Inc. climbed 86 cents to $50.33 in Germany after Morgan Stanley raised the stock to ``overweight&#39;&#39; from ``equal-weight.&#39;&#39; JPMorgan lifted its recommendation to ``overweight&#39;&#39; from ``neutral.&#39;&#39; Indexes of commodities, energy, consumer and industrial shares touched all-time highs on June 1 after hiring almost doubled and inflation trailed economists&#39; forecasts. The S&P 500 added 5.72, or 0.4 percent, to 1536.34. The Dow average increased 40.47, or 0.3 percent, to 13,668.11. The Nasdaq Composite Index climbed 9.4, or 0.4 percent, to 2613.92. To contact the reporter on this story: Marco Bertacche in Milan at at Last Updated: June 4, 2007 07:11 EDT Related Media on Demand Bevan of CCLA Sees Rival Bids for Dow Jones Takeover Factory Orders in U.S. Increased 0.3 Percent in April, Less Than Estimated Loews, XTO Will Buy Dominion&#39;s Onshore Oil, Gas