. I don't think anyone should make any inferences about the U.S. market from an overextended Chinese market," said Brian Gendreau, investment strategist at ING Investment Management in New York. The Standard & Poor's 500 Index (.SPX: gained 2.84 points, or 0.18 percent, to 1,539.18, finishing at a record for the fourth straight session. The Dow Jones industrial average (.DJI: rose 8.21 points, or 0.06 percent, to end at a record 13,676.32.The Nasdaq Composite Index (.IXIC: advanced 4.37 points, or 0.17 percent, to close at 2,618.29. &copy; Reuters 2007. All rights reserved. Editors Choice: Best pictures from the last 24 hours. START News Content Page Tags 'Text' | 'Picture' | 'Slideshow' | 'Video' ie. headline for article ie. headline for article END News Content Page Tags In quotes: Subprime fallout The stories behind the deals and the deal-makers as seen and heard by Reuters reporters covering mergers & acquisitions and Wall Street. Deals of the Day: Read the latest headlines Rounding up the papers US STOCKS-Dow, S&P close at records as energy shares rise Top Company Research Reports on Reuters.com Qantas Airways Ltd. [QAN] Globalstar IPO Update [GSAT] MFS Research Bond Fund [MRBFX] Reuters in Second Life Reuters is the world's largest international multimedia news agency, providing investing news, world news, business news, technology news, headline news, small business news, news alerts, personal finance, stock market, and mutual funds information available on Reuters.com, video, mobile, and interactive television platforms. Reuters journalists are subject to the Reuters Editorial Handbook which requires fair presentation and disclosure of relevant interests. START OF SmartSource Data Collector TAG Copyright (c) 1996-2006 WebTrends Inc. All rights reserved. END OF SmartSource Data Collector TAG
