s to 33 of its entertainment sites. Viacom, meanwhile, is famously at odds with Google over a billion-dollar copyright infringement lawsuit over YouTube video clips. In another strategic move to bolster its place in the online advertising market, Yahoo purchased ad exchange Right Media More from News.com on this story's topics Create an email alert Create an email alert Create an email alert Beyond The PR - File A Law Suit Jun 4, 2007, 10:01 AM PDT Read more comments > Photos: Kids groove on tech at camp Along with their bug juice and canoes, today's campers use Flash, Java and the 3D video game applications of the pros. In ad wars, Yahoo aims for Right touch Yahoo profit down from a year ago Yahoo, Viacom strike search deal Viacom sues Google over YouTube clips Two top Yahoo execs to leave in reorg Get this story's "Big Picture" > Generations of 'Star Wars' enthusiasts come together Marketing strategies for the Web 2.0 era Executives discuss how the modern Web is impacting IT Watch more videos > Companies try eBay to sell themselves (USATODAY.com) Microsoft to Offer Improved Tools to Search Books Yahoo! Europe! upgrades! ad! platform! Live: All Things D Wednesday Morning Session with Ballmer and the Surface Table Millions of Addresses, Thousands of Sites, One Business Cheap Calling: Rumor: Google Testing Outbound Calling from Google Talk? Google to Focus on Software: CEO Get more news around the Web with News.com Extra > Aligning CIO & CEO visions What CIOs need to know It&#39;s a simple truth. The closer you and your CEO see things, the greater your chance for success. Our exclusive report can help you get there&mdash;and help your business grow. Get the report featuring the views of 765 CEOs on innovation. What CEOs think: Innovation Insights for CIOs Learn How CIOs can deliver strategic success for their enterprises The New CIO: Beyond Technology Learn how CIOs become heroes "Change Catalyst: How Technology Innovations Transformed the Entertainment Business." Le